# Documentation Standards, glob pattern(s) for applicable files: docs/**/*.md

## Documentation Structure

All documentation files MUST follow this structure:

```markdown
---
title: Page Title
description: Brief description
---

# Page Title

## Overview
[Introduction]

## Sections
[Content]

## Examples
[Code examples]

## See Also
[Related links]
```

## Frontmatter Requirements

Every documentation file MUST include:

- `title`: Page title
- `description`: Brief description (used in navigation)

Optional:
- `category`: Category for navigation
- `order`: Display order
- `tags`: Tags for search

## Code Examples

Code examples MUST:
- Be executable (tested)
- Include imports
- Show complete patterns
- Include error handling where relevant

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD: Complete example
import { createLens } from '@3lens/runtime';

const lens = createLens({
  capture: { mode: 'STANDARD' }
});

// ❌ BAD: Incomplete example
const lens = createLens();
```

## Cross-References

Documentation MUST cross-reference:
- Related contracts: `[Contract Name](agents/contracts/[name].md)`
- Related playbooks: `[Playbook Name](agents/playbooks/[name].md)`
- Related skills: `[Skill Name](.cursor/skills/[name]/SKILL.md)`
- Related commands: `[Command Name](.cursor/commands/[name].md)`

## API Documentation

API documentation MUST:
- Include TypeScript types
- Show parameter descriptions
- Include return types
- Show examples
- Document errors/exceptions

## Contract Documentation

Contract documentation MUST:
- Explain purpose clearly
- List all invariants
- Describe degradation rules
- Include acceptance tests
- List anti-goals

## Example Documentation

Example documentation MUST:
- Include setup instructions
- Show complete working code
- Explain key concepts
- Link to related docs
- Include troubleshooting

